items.sentence: You weren't surprised I wasn't able to do that, were you?
You weren't surprised I didn't want to do that, were you?
You weren't surprised I didn't need to do that, were you?
You weren't surprised I didn't have to do that, were you?
I hope that Tom does everything that he's promised to do.
I think Tom bought the house he was looking at last week.
Tom felt a sudden urge to smash the window with his fist.
Tom knows better than to walk home by himself after dark.
If I declare bankruptcy, will I be able to keep my house?
I was standing next to Tom in the back of the auditorium.
